#User feedback

Feedback1:

User 1 was able to log in to the application and navigate through the system without experiencing any major difficulties.
The user reported that the overall layout of the dashboard was clear and well organized. The health information displayed 
on the screen was easy to understand, and the progress indicators helped the user quickly view their daily health activities. 
In addition, the user mentioned that the icons and navigation buttons were easy to recognize, which made it easier to move between
different sections of the application.

Feedback2:

User 2 was able to complete most of the testing tasks successfully, including logging into the application, navigating to the dashboard,
and viewing health progress information. However, the user initially hesitated when trying to locate the activity recording section for 
the first time. After exploring the interface for a short time, the user was able to understand the structure of the application and 
complete the tasks without further issues. The user commented that the application interface was simple and user-friendly once the main
features were identified.

Feedback3:

User 3 also reported a positive experience while using the prototype. The user mentioned that the interface design was visually clear and 
easy to follow, which made the system comfortable to use. The user particularly liked the progress indicators shown on the dashboard, as 
they helped provide a quick overview of daily health activities. In addition, the health logging feature was considered straightforward 
and easy to use, allowing users to quickly record their daily health information. Overall, the feedback from the three users indicated 
that the prototype was generally easy to understand and navigate. The testing results showed that users were able to perform the main tasks 
of the system successfully. The feedback also provided useful insights that helped the development team identify small areas where the interface could be improved to further enhance the user experience.
